<A NAME="topicToolCalibration"></A>

<H2>Calibration Tool</H2>
This tool is used to calibrate the mesh.<P>

<H2>Usage</H2>

<OL>

<LI>
If the mesh has GPS information it will ask if you want to calibrate using it, press "OK" to apply the GPS calibration or "Cancel" to abort the operation. If the mesh doesn't have GPS information, or you don't want to use it, follow the next steps.

<LI>
Measure some know distance using the <A HREF="helpMart-0019.htm">measure tool</A>.

<LI>
Start the tool using the icon in the toolbar.

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><img align="center" src="calib0.png"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<LI>
Add the correct distance with the measure unit in the "Calibration" dialog, press "OK" to apply the calibration or "Cancel" to abort the operation.

<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><img align="center" src="calib02.png"> </CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<LI>
The mesh will be calibrated, further measures will use this as reference.

</OL>

<H2>Shortcuts</H2>

<UL>
<LI> Ctrl + I - Enable/disable the calibration tool.
</UL>

</FONT></BODY></HTML>